<p>SI (International System of Units) provides the foundation for scientific measurement. Measures
includes all seven SI base units and common derived units.</p>

<h3>Base Units</h3>

<pre><code class="language-lean">open Measures.Units.SI

def length := 5.0 *: meter      -- Length
def mass := 70.0 *: kilogram    -- Mass
def duration := 60.0 *: second  -- Time
def current := 1.5 *: ampere    -- Electric current
def temp := 300.0 *: kelvin     -- Temperature
def amount := 2.0 *: mole       -- Amount of substance
def intensity := 100.0 *: candela  -- Luminous intensity</code></pre>

<h3>Derived Units</h3>

<pre><code class="language-lean">-- Energy and power
def energy := 1000.0 *: joule   -- J = kg·m²/s²
def power := 100.0 *: watt      -- W = J/s

-- Force
def force := 9.8 *: newton      -- N = kg·m/s²

-- Velocity and acceleration
def velocity := 25.0 *: meterPerSecond         -- m/s
def accel := 9.8 *: meterPerSecondSquared      -- m/s²</code></pre>

<h3>SI Prefixes</h3>

<p>Standard SI prefixes are available for scaling units:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">-- Large scales
def marathon := 42.195 *: kilometer    -- 10³ meters
def gigabyte := 8.0 *: gigajoule       -- 10⁹ joules

-- Small scales
def wavelength := 550.0 *: nanometer   -- 10⁻⁹ meters
def microseconds := 100.0 *: microsecond
def milligrams := 250.0 *: milligram</code></pre>

